<section>
<title>When Is It Safe to Use These Methods?</title>
<body>
<p>As we mentioned before, one of the most important things to learn with any inference method is the conditions under which it is safe to use it.</p>
<p>As we did for the mean, the assumption we made in order to develop the methods in this unit was
                    that the sampling distribution of the sample proportion, <m:math
                        overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mover>
                                <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                                <m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
                            </m:mover>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math>,<?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T115009-0500" comment="Is new eording OK? I&apos;m trying to avoid saying &quot;distribution&quot; twice)"?>
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T114922-0500"?>is
                    roughly<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T114926-0500" content="has a"?>
                    normal<?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T114932-0500" content=" distribution"?>.<?oxy_comment_end?>
                    Recall from module 4 of the Probability unit that
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T115028-0500"?>the
                    <?oxy_insert_end?>conditions under which this happens are that
                        <?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T115116-0500" comment="Suggest using asterisks for multiplication rather than dots here and below"?><m:math
                        overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>⋅</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
                            <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math> and <m:math overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>⋅</m:mo>
                            <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                                <m:mrow>
                                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                                    <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                                </m:mrow>
                            </m:mfenced>
                            <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
                            <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math>.<?oxy_comment_end?> Since p is unknown, we will replace it
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T115137-0500"?>with<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T115136-0500" content="by"?>
                    its estimate, the sample proportion, and set</p>
<p>
<m:math overflow="scroll">
<m:mrow>
<m:mi>n</m:mi>
<m:mo>⋅</m:mo>
<m:mover>
<m:mi>p</m:mi>
<m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
</m:mover>
<m:mo>≥</m:mo>
<m:mn>10</m:mn>
</m:mrow>
</m:math> and <m:math overflow="scroll">
<m:mrow>
<m:mi>n</m:mi>
<m:mo>⋅</m:mo>
<m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
<m:mrow>
<m:mn>1</m:mn>
<m:mo>−</m:mo>
<m:mover>
<m:mi>p</m:mi>
<m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
</m:mover>
</m:mrow>
</m:mfenced>
<m:mo>≥</m:mo>
<m:mn>10</m:mn>
</m:mrow>
</m:math>
</p>
<p>to be the conditions under which it is safe to use the methods we developed in this section.</p>
<p> </p>
</body>
